Bombardier May Win U.K. Government Train Deal, Sunday Times Says

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   B r o w n i n g
-- 
2011-09-11T05:29:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-11/bombardier-may-win-u-k-government-train-deal-sunday-times-says.html
Bombardier Inc. (BBD/B)  may win a 120
million-pound ($191 million) U.K. government contract to build
electric trains, the Sunday Times reported, citing unidentified
people familiar with the matter.  The contract to build 57 trains for the Cross Country rail
line would safeguard 1,600 jobs at a plant in Derby,  England ,
which had been threatened with closure, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan Browning in London at 
 jbrowning9@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
